1
00:00:00,742 --> 00:00:03,203
星际之门之亚特兰蒂斯 前情提要
Previously, on Stargate Atlantis...

2
00:00:03,244 --> 00:00:04,287
我们对幽灵知道些多少？
What do we know about the Wraith?

3
00:00:04,329 --> 00:00:08,625
所知不多  其中之一就是它们是打败古人的敌人
One of the few things we do know is that
they are the enemy that defeated the ancients.

4
00:00:09,459 --> 00:00:12,795
有时 几百年后它们才会再次醒来
Sometimes, a few hundred years
will pass before they awaken again.

5
00:00:12,837 --> 00:00:15,298
我们已经到过很多很多星球了
We have visited many, many worlds.

6
00:00:15,715 --> 00:00:18,092
据有所知 没有哪个没有被幽灵所蹂躏的
I know of none untouched by the Wraith.

7
00:00:18,134 --> 00:00:22,680
你们注定是会灭亡的
就跟许多与你们同路的人类一样
You are doomed, as are any
humans that stand in our way.

8
00:00:22,722 --> 00:00:25,475
古人曾经研究过"升天"
The ancients were researching ascension.

9
00:00:25,516 --> 00:00:26,768
"升天"到底是什么意思?
What exactly is ascension?

10
00:00:26,809 --> 00:00:28,436
一个他们所能够达到的更高级的阶段
An advanced stage of being where they were able

11
00:00:28,478 --> 00:00:29,938
让他们摆脱自己的肉身
to rid themselves of their physical bodies

12
00:00:29,979 --> 00:00:31,397
上升到一个更高的存在形式
and rise to a higher plane of existence,

13
00:00:31,439 --> 00:00:34,025
最终他们纯粹以能量形式生存
one in which they live as pure energy.

14
00:00:42,825 --> 00:00:44,744
- 我数到二, 准备好了么?
- 是的, 长官
- I count two. How about you?
- Yes, sir.

15
00:00:44,911 --> 00:00:47,413
- 我建议现在立刻进行回击
- 我正在努力
- I recommend shooting back any time now.
- I'm trying.

16
00:00:47,914 --> 00:00:50,750
- 刚才的一击一定造成了一些损坏. McKay?
- 我就去看看
- That hit must've caused some damage. McKay?
- I'm on it.

17
00:00:51,125 --> 00:00:52,502
它们是从哪里来的?
Where did they come from?

18
00:00:53,503 --> 00:00:56,256
她是对的  那些看似飞标的物体正是短程战斗机
She's right. The darts are short-range fighters.

19
00:00:56,297 --> 00:00:58,675
这附近一定有一艘母船
There's probably a hive ship around here somewhere.

20
00:00:58,841 --> 00:01:00,718
- 那么我们应该马上离开这里
- 是的
- Then we need to get out of here.
- Yes, we do.

21
00:01:00,927 --> 00:01:03,596
星际之门在另外一边
行星的另一侧
The Stargate's the other way,
on the other side of the planet.

22
00:01:03,638 --> 00:01:05,431
是, 我们现在简直就像是在观光漫步  McKay!
Yeah, we're taking the scenic route. McKay!

23
00:01:05,598 --> 00:01:06,641
我就快搞定了!
I've almost there!

24
00:01:07,767 --> 00:01:09,018
有一个正在我们身后!
There's one on our tail!

25
00:01:09,060 --> 00:01:12,146
谢谢, 我也知道
把你的眼睛用来盯住另外那个
Thank you, I know all about that one.
Keep your eye on the other one.

26
00:01:12,272 --> 00:01:13,273
OK, 你应该可以用武器了
Okay, you should have weapons now.

27
00:01:13,314 --> 00:01:14,440
- 不行
- 你确信?
- Negative.
- Are you sure?

28
00:01:14,524 --> 00:01:16,526
- 肯定
- 我非常肯定我已经把它修好了
- Positive!
- I'm pretty sure I fixed it.

29
00:01:17,110 --> 00:01:19,070
好吧, 实际上你根本就没有!
Well, obviously you didn't!

30
00:01:20,780 --> 00:01:22,949
也许你可以在大气层中把它们甩掉
Perhaps you can lose them in
the atmosphere of the planet.

31
00:01:23,032 --> 00:01:24,492
两点钟方向又来了两艘
Two more darts on our two o'clock.

32
00:01:24,534 --> 00:01:25,785
我看到了. McKay!
I see them. McKay!

33
00:01:25,827 --> 00:01:27,579
我看起来可不是正在故意妨碍你
It's not like I'm holding back on you.

34
00:01:43,553 --> 00:01:44,554
抓好!
Hang on!

35
00:01:57,734 --> 00:01:59,235
幽灵的梭镖飞船已经被消灭了
The Wraith darts have been destroyed.

36
00:01:59,277 --> 00:02:00,486
好, 这是件好事
Well, that's a good thing.

37
00:02:02,488 --> 00:02:07,118
我敢肯定我们已经死了
你们认为我们现在死了么
I thought for sure we were dead.
Didn't you think we were dead?

38
00:02:07,160 --> 00:02:08,161
那到底是什么?
What the hell was that?

39
00:02:08,203 --> 00:02:09,996
某种, 嗯, 能量武器?
Some sort of, uh, energy weapon?

40
00:02:10,663 --> 00:02:12,790
你说我们发现了什么?
What do you say we find out?

41
00:03:10,506 --> 00:03:16,220
星际之门之亚特兰蒂斯
第一季第14集 避难所
Season 1: Episode 14 Sanctuary

42
00:03:23,236 --> 00:03:26,990
那么, 肯定一下, 我们仍然...
So just to confirm, we're all still...

43
00:03:28,157 --> 00:03:29,242
明确的说还没有死
definitely not dead.

44
00:03:29,742 --> 00:03:31,744
我感觉活得很好
I feel very much alive.

45
00:03:31,786 --> 00:03:32,912
很好  我也一样
Good. Same here.

46
00:03:32,954 --> 00:03:34,455
我很想知道那到底是什么
I wish I knew what that was.

47
00:03:34,497 --> 00:03:35,415
看起来像闪电
Looked like lightning.

48
00:03:35,456 --> 00:03:36,457
太空闪电?
Space lightning?

49
00:03:36,499 --> 00:03:39,961
我已经说了, 那是某种能量武器
显然是它摧毁了幽灵的飞船
I already said, it's some sort of an energy weapon,
one that apparently destroys Wraith darts.

50
00:03:40,003 --> 00:03:42,088
不错, 但为什么摧毁的只是它们而不是我们?
Nice, but why them and not us?

51
00:03:42,130 --> 00:03:46,009
好吧, 假设我们仍然还活着
而且也没有任何损坏
Well, assuming that we're still alive,
and there doesn't appear to be any damage

52
00:03:46,050 --> 00:03:48,469
从脉搏的结果来看
我想我们可以确实的得出结论, 嗯...
as a result of the pulse,
I think we can safely conclude that, uh...

53
00:03:53,474 --> 00:03:54,058
我什么也没有得到
I got nothing.

54
00:03:54,434 --> 00:03:56,519
我的意思是, 我没有得到什么结论
I mean, I got nothing to conclude.

55
00:03:56,561 --> 00:03:58,438
我只是为了说话而说话
I'm just talking for the sake of talking.

56
00:03:58,479 --> 00:03:59,230
你确信你还好吧?
Are you sure you're okay?

57
00:03:59,272 --> 00:04:01,524
你知道我是多么憎恶死亡?
You know how much I hate certain death?

58
00:04:01,566 --> 00:04:02,734
你还活着
You're alive.

59
00:04:02,775 --> 00:04:05,820
这会是某种自然现象么?
Could something like that be naturally occurring?

60
00:04:05,862 --> 00:04:08,031
肯定不是
My money's on non-naturally occurring.

61
00:04:08,072 --> 00:04:09,449
有没可能是古人留下的武器?
Like a weapon the ancients left behind?

62
00:04:10,033 --> 00:04:12,660
任何有如此威力的武器
的能量来源一定是...
And any weapon that impressive
would have to be powered by...

63
00:04:12,702 --> 00:04:14,078
- ... 零点模块
- 对
- ... a zero-point module.
- That's right.

64
00:04:14,120 --> 00:04:15,580
好吧, 我们需要下去
All right, we need to get down there.

65
00:04:15,622 --> 00:04:18,333
不管怎么说, 在我们返回亚特兰蒂斯之前
需要检查一下有没有什么损坏
I've got to check for damage anyway
before we head back to Atlantis.

66
00:04:32,513 --> 00:04:36,309
如果下面某个地方确实有这种武器
长官, 那也肯定不是这些家伙造的
If there is a weapon somewhere down here,
sir, these folks didn't build it.

67
00:04:36,726 --> 00:04:37,685
不是这些孩子们
Not these kids.

68
00:04:39,187 --> 00:04:40,480
你发现什么了么?
You picking up anything?

69
00:04:40,521 --> 00:04:42,732
我正在检查一切
没有什么值得关注的
I'm picking up everything,
just nothing worth mentioning.

70
00:04:43,149 --> 00:04:45,735
这些人看起来跟你比较亲近, Teyla?
These folks look familiar to you, Teyla?

71
00:04:45,777 --> 00:04:49,030
星际之门是在轨道中, 少校
我的人们不可能探险来到这里
The Stargate is in orbit, Major.
My people could never have ventured here.

72
00:04:49,656 --> 00:04:52,992
对
那我们去探险如何?
Right.
What say we venture?

73
00:05:17,225 --> 00:05:18,226
嗨
Hi.

74
00:05:21,854 --> 00:05:23,606
没事. 我们很友好
It's okay. We're friendly.

75
00:05:25,275 --> 00:05:25,858
嗨
Hi.

76
00:05:28,528 --> 00:05:31,197
看起来他们好像没有见过村子外的人.
It is likely they have never seen
anyone from outside their village.

77
00:05:45,503 --> 00:05:46,337
欢迎
Welcome.

78
00:05:47,714 --> 00:05:51,885
我叫Zarah, Proculis的一个修道士
I am Zarah, one of the abbots of Proculis.

79
00:05:52,427 --> 00:05:54,470
我是John. John Sheppard.
I'm John. John Sheppard.

80
00:05:54,512 --> 00:05:57,974
这是Teyla, Ford中尉, 以及McKay博士
This is Teyla, lieutenant Ford, and dr. McKay.

81
00:06:00,310 --> 00:06:01,978
请, 来吧
Please, come.

82
00:06:24,042 --> 00:06:31,966
这是我生命中第一次看到
其他国家的人来到我们这里
This is the first time at least in my own lifetime
that people from another land have come to us.

83
00:06:33,009 --> 00:06:34,093
嗯, 我们是坐飞船来的
Well, we came by ship.

84
00:06:36,971 --> 00:06:42,769
一个可以飞的东西
可以把我们从一个星球带到另外一个星球
A flying thing that allows us
to move from one world to another.

85
00:06:42,810 --> 00:06:44,187
另一个星球?
Another world?

86
00:06:44,437 --> 00:06:47,148
从你们夜晚看到的星星中间
From among the stars you see in the night sky.

87
00:06:48,441 --> 00:06:50,443
我们是和平的探险者
We are peaceful explorers.

88
00:06:51,778 --> 00:06:55,573
那么感谢Athar把你们安全的带到这里
Then glory to Athar for bringing you here safely.

89
00:06:56,282 --> 00:06:57,575
Athar?
Athar?

90
00:06:58,117 --> 00:07:01,746
我们所有人的供应者... 和保护者
The provider... and protector of all.

91
00:07:01,955 --> 00:07:03,373
你们应该知道
Surely you know.

92
00:07:03,623 --> 00:07:06,960
Athar是我们所知诸多星辰中的一个
Athar is known by many names among the stars.

93
00:07:07,001 --> 00:07:09,712
嗯... Athar在周围么?
Is, um... Athar around?

94
00:07:09,921 --> 00:07:12,799
我们很想跟他谈谈.
我们是, 嗯, 朋友
We'd love to talk to him.
We're, uh, friends.

95
00:07:13,007 --> 00:07:17,220
Athar是我们所有人的朋友, 而且他永远和我们在一起
Athar is friend to all, and with us always.

96
00:07:17,887 --> 00:07:20,098
即使是现在
Even now.

97
00:07:20,139 --> 00:07:21,474
当然
Of course.

98
00:07:23,142 --> 00:07:24,102
嗨, Athar.
Hi, Athar.

99
00:07:24,143 --> 00:07:28,314
McKay博士的意思是
我们想表达我们的谢意
What dr. McKay means is that
we wish to offer our thanks.

100
00:07:28,356 --> 00:07:31,192
我们被幽灵袭击
We were attacked by the Wraith
and would have been killed,

101
00:07:31,234 --> 00:07:33,361
如果不是Athar的干涉
我们几乎就被它们杀死了
were it not for Athar's intervention.

102
00:07:34,237 --> 00:07:35,113
"幽灵"?
"Wraith"?

103
00:07:35,822 --> 00:07:39,993
苍白的皮肤, 深陷的眼睛
用手将你的生命吸取出来
Pale skin, sunken eyes,
suck the life out of you with their hands?

104
00:07:40,243 --> 00:07:43,079
我们从来没有碰到过这种事情
We have never encountered such beings.

105
00:07:43,413 --> 00:07:44,455
从来?
Never?

106
00:07:46,082 --> 00:07:49,043
而且你们的历史中也从来没有提及?
And there is no mention of them in your history?

107
00:07:49,085 --> 00:07:49,919
没有
None.

108
00:07:49,961 --> 00:07:54,716
我可以向你保证, 几千年来
我们都生活在和平之中
I can assure you that for many thousands of years,
we have lived here in peace.

109
00:07:57,802 --> 00:07:59,846
能让我们离开一会儿么?
Could you excuse us for a moment?

110
00:08:01,180 --> 00:08:06,394
当然. 不过不是现在  在我们会见Chaya之前
我要告诉其他的修道士你们的到来
Of course. Please, I must tell the other abbots
of your arrival before we go to meet with Chaya.

111
00:08:06,436 --> 00:08:08,187
那么Chaya又是...
And Chaya is...

112
00:08:08,229 --> 00:08:10,565
Athar的女祭司
The high priestess of Athar.

113
00:08:11,691 --> 00:08:13,693
这对我们人民来说是伟大的一天
This is a great day for our people.

114
00:08:17,405 --> 00:08:18,448
对我们也是
Ours too.

115
00:08:22,202 --> 00:08:24,120
不是开玩笑
这真的有作用?
I'm not kidding. This could really work.

116
00:08:24,162 --> 00:08:25,205
我同意, 少校
I agree, Major.

117
00:08:25,246 --> 00:08:29,876
在这个星系中, 所有我访问过的星球
都曾经遭受过幽灵的蹂躏
Every inhabited world I have encountered
in this galaxy has been ravaged by the Wraith.

118
00:08:29,918 --> 00:08:32,212
嗯, 这个星球受到了古人的武器的保护
Well, this planet is protected
by an Ancient weapon.

119
00:08:32,253 --> 00:08:33,463
这正好可以肯定这一点
This just confirms it.

120
00:08:33,504 --> 00:08:33,838
是么?
Does it?

121
00:08:33,880 --> 00:08:35,006
好吧, 没有第二种解释了
Well, there's no other explanation.

122
00:08:35,048 --> 00:08:37,592
我的意思是, 那种东西对能量的需求
是相当惊人的
I mean, the power requirements of
something like that must be astronomical.

123
00:08:37,634 --> 00:08:39,177
只有 Z.P.M. 可以产生那种能量
Only a Z.P.M. could generate that.

124
00:08:39,219 --> 00:08:42,513
而且现在...在技术上
他们还没有发达到那种地步
And yet... they do not appear
to be technologically advanced.

125
00:08:42,555 --> 00:08:47,185
除非刚才那个家伙在撒谎
但他不像是会撒谎的那种人
Unless that guy was lying,
but he doesn't seem like the lying type.

126
00:08:47,227 --> 00:08:49,854
那么, 自动防御?
So, automated defenses.

127
00:08:49,896 --> 00:08:54,817
想象一下, 有这样一个星球
可以把其他星球上的难民转移过来, 和平的生活
Imagine a world where displaced refugees from
dozens of planets could come and live in peace,

128
00:08:54,859 --> 00:08:57,195
不用再担心会被幽灵抓去
without fear of being culled by the Wraith.

129
00:08:57,278 --> 00:08:59,572
也许我们可以跟他们谈判
Maybe we can negotiate some kind of treaty.

130
00:08:59,614 --> 00:09:01,699
最好我们能被允许使用那个武器, 那个Z.P.M.
We just need access to that
weapon better still, the Z.P.M.,

131
00:09:01,991 --> 00:09:03,868
实在不行我们就去偷了它
not that we'd steal it or anything.

132
00:09:03,910 --> 00:09:06,287
我们应该尽量光明正大一点
Let's just try to stay on our best behavior.

133
00:09:06,329 --> 00:09:07,997
我总是光明正大的
I'm always on my best behavior.

134
00:09:11,918 --> 00:09:14,546
有多远?
How much farther?

135
00:09:14,587 --> 00:09:15,672
不是很远
Not very.

136
00:09:15,713 --> 00:09:16,714
噢, 很好
Oh, good.

137
00:09:18,675 --> 00:09:20,218
瞧? 我们本可以坐飞船去的
See? We could have taken the jumper.

138
00:09:20,260 --> 00:09:21,427
对你来说, 锻炼一下不是坏事
The exercise is good for you.

139
00:09:22,136 --> 00:09:24,013
Chaya住得离你的人民确实远了点
Chaya does live pretty far from your people.

140
00:09:24,764 --> 00:09:27,976
这很不寻常, 少校
牧师竟然不是住在社区当中
It is not uncommon, Major,
for clerics to live apart from the community.

141
00:09:58,047 --> 00:09:59,173
以伟大Athar的名义
Glory to Athar.

142
00:09:59,215 --> 00:10:00,925
欢迎, 请就便
Welcome, and rest.

143
00:10:00,967 --> 00:10:02,635
谢谢你, 女教士
Thank you, sister.

144
00:10:04,721 --> 00:10:06,097
对Proculis来说,  你们都是新人
You are new to Proculis.

145
00:10:06,139 --> 00:10:08,099
是的,  我们...
Yes. We're, uh...

146
00:10:08,141 --> 00:10:09,601
我们是"崭新的", 事实上
we're brand new, in fact.

147
00:10:09,642 --> 00:10:12,562
John Sheppard少校
Major John Sheppard.

148
00:10:12,604 --> 00:10:15,440
我的名字叫Chaya Sar.
I am called Chaya Sar.

149
00:10:15,815 --> 00:10:17,191
那么你是...
And you are...

150
00:10:17,233 --> 00:10:18,484
Teyla...
Teyla...

151
00:10:18,985 --> 00:10:21,112
Ford中尉, 以及McKay博士
Lieutenant Ford, and Dr. McKay.

152
00:10:21,154 --> 00:10:22,655
她是怎么知道的?
How did she know that?

153
00:10:22,697 --> 00:10:23,573
噢, 这都不懂
Oh, please.

154
00:10:23,656 --> 00:10:24,991
有个修道士先来过了
One of the abbots ran ahead.

155
00:10:25,033 --> 00:10:26,993
很高兴见到你, Chaya.
It's a pleasure to meet you, Chaya.

156
00:10:28,411 --> 00:10:30,330
走了这么远, 你们一定累了吧
You must be tired after your long journey.

157
00:10:30,371 --> 00:10:32,248
我可以去准备些茶么?
Shall I prepare some tea for us?

158
00:10:34,000 --> 00:10:36,669
我想我们也正想这么说
I was hoping you were going to say just that.

159
00:10:40,423 --> 00:10:42,258
那么那些幽灵是从哪里来的?
And where do they come from, these Wraith?

160
00:10:42,300 --> 00:10:46,179
看起来它们在这个星系中无处不在
They seem to be everywhere in this galaxy,
and they appear to have been on top

161
00:10:46,221 --> 00:10:47,513
而且看起来在很长一段时间内
它们处于食物链的顶端
of the food chain for a long time.

162
00:10:47,555 --> 00:10:48,723
这太恐怖了
It's terrifying.

163
00:10:49,849 --> 00:10:51,267
确实很恐怖
Truly terrifying.

164
00:10:52,018 --> 00:10:54,312
我非常为你的人民担心, Teyla.
My heart goes out to your people, Teyla.

165
00:10:54,354 --> 00:10:56,606
遭受厄运的不仅仅只是我的人民, Chaya.
It is not only my people who suffer, Chaya.

166
00:10:56,648 --> 00:10:59,275
幽灵已经从长时间的睡眠中苏醒过来了
The Wraith have awakened from a long sleep,

167
00:10:59,317 --> 00:11:03,238
不过在已经开始的选择中(指幽灵选择食物)
这整个星球看起来却是安全的
and this entire world is safe from
the culling that has already begun.

168
00:11:03,613 --> 00:11:08,785
即便是亚特兰蒂斯, 即使有那么多的奇迹
也可能经受不住冲击
Even Atlantis, with all its wonder,
may not survive the onslaught.

169
00:11:08,826 --> 00:11:13,915
我们共同希望Athar
允许在Proculis, 也就是在这里, 建立避难所
It is our hope that Athar
could grant sanctuary here on Proculis.

170
00:11:13,957 --> 00:11:15,083
避难所?
Sanctuary?

171
00:11:17,835 --> 00:11:18,878
为如此之多的人?
For so many?

172
00:11:18,920 --> 00:11:23,091
嗯, 我们并不是说这个星系中所有的人
都会出现在你的门口
Well, we're not talking about everybody
in the galaxy showing up on your doorstep.

173
00:11:23,132 --> 00:11:24,884
这个行星很大, 女士
This planet is pretty big, ma'am.

174
00:11:24,926 --> 00:11:26,803
而且大部分无人居住
And it is largely uninhabited.

175
00:11:26,844 --> 00:11:30,056
更重要的是
它受到你们那种武器的保护
More importantly,
it is protected by that weapon of yours.

176
00:11:30,098 --> 00:11:31,266
武器?
Weapon?

177
00:11:31,307 --> 00:11:33,393
我想在Proculis没有这种东西
I am aware of no such thing on Proculis.

178
00:11:35,853 --> 00:11:37,438
你确信?
Are you sure about that?

179
00:11:37,480 --> 00:11:38,565
是的
Yes.

180
00:11:38,606 --> 00:11:39,857
噢, 不要这样
Oh, please.

181
00:11:40,191 --> 00:11:41,943
Rodney, 表现好一点
Rodney, best behavior.

182
00:11:41,985 --> 00:11:43,861
这跟我们得到的已经是一样好了, 少校
This is as good as it gets, Major.

183
00:11:43,903 --> 00:11:47,907
Chaya, 我们还活着的唯一原因就是
Chaya, the only reason we're alive
is because of a powerful energy weapon

184
00:11:47,949 --> 00:11:49,993
从这个星球表面某处发射出来的
某种强大的能量武器
that emanated from somewhere
on the surface of this planet.

185
00:11:50,034 --> 00:11:52,453
它摧毁了朝我们射击的飞船
It destroyed the ships that were shooting at us.

186
00:11:52,495 --> 00:11:54,497
正是那个武器使幽灵无法靠近
That weapon is what's keeping the Wraith away.

187
00:11:54,539 --> 00:11:55,415
不,  McKay博士
No, Dr. McKay.

188
00:11:55,456 --> 00:11:57,292
是Athar保护了你们
It was Athar who protected you.

189
00:11:57,333 --> 00:11:58,418
Athar?
Athar?

190
00:11:58,459 --> 00:11:59,419
是的
Yes.

191
00:11:59,460 --> 00:12:01,296
Athar看到你们需要他
Athar saw you were in need.

192
00:12:02,630 --> 00:12:05,341
Chaya, 有非常多的人就像...
Chaya, there are a lot of people just like...

193
00:12:07,969 --> 00:12:11,389
你和我, 都需要他, 因为幽灵
you and me, who are in need because of the Wraith.

194
00:12:11,431 --> 00:12:17,979
你们在这里所拥有的,  也就是Athar提供给你们的
是非常稀有的东西...
What you have here, what Athar
has provided you, is a very rare thing...

195
00:12:19,814 --> 00:12:21,816
不过我们需要把他也提供给更多的人
but we have a lot to offer too.

196
00:12:21,858 --> 00:12:25,445
这就是朋友所应该做的
他们共同分享
That's what friends do. They share.

197
00:12:26,779 --> 00:12:28,698
我想我们可以互相帮助
I think we could help each other.

198
00:12:30,241 --> 00:12:31,451
我知道了
I understand.

199
00:12:33,244 --> 00:12:35,079
我现在应该和她商量一下
I shall consult with her now.

200
00:12:38,625 --> 00:12:42,128
请待在这里
我不知道这需要多长时间
Please stay here.
I don't know how long this will take.

201
00:12:44,505 --> 00:12:45,256
谢谢
Thank you.

202
00:12:46,090 --> 00:12:48,760
"Athar提供给你们的?"
"What Athar provides for you?"

203
00:12:48,801 --> 00:12:49,844
你也想承认这些?
You're buying into this?

204
00:12:49,886 --> 00:12:51,221
Rodney...
Rodney...

205
00:12:51,262 --> 00:12:53,723
这些虔诚的人们怎么可能
不认真对待他们自己的宗教?
what religious people don't
take their religion seriously?

206
00:12:53,765 --> 00:12:55,475
那个武器并不是我们想象出来的, 少校
We didn't imagine that weapon, Major.

207
00:12:55,516 --> 00:12:58,269
我们亲眼看见了
而且我们也看见了它的能力
We saw it with our own eyes,
and we saw what it was capable of.

208
00:12:58,311 --> 00:12:59,354
是的, 我们确实看见了
Yes, we did.

209
00:12:59,395 --> 00:13:02,899
也许Chaya只是不知道那个武器的存在
Perhaps Chaya is simply
unaware of the weapon's existence.

210
00:13:02,941 --> 00:13:06,402
或许她知道, 不过她不想让我们也知道
Or she knows, and she wants
to keep it a secret from us.

211
00:13:06,653 --> 00:13:08,529
从她对我说话的语气来看
也不像是在说谎
She doesn't strike me
as the lying type either.

212
00:13:11,199 --> 00:13:14,661
好吧, 我们就看看Athar会说些什么
All right, let's just see
what Athar has to say.

213
00:13:16,329 --> 00:13:19,499
就是说, "别管幕后那人是怎么说的", 是么?
So, "pay no attention to
the man behind the curtain," hmm?

214
00:13:19,541 --> 00:13:20,542
很对
Exactly.

215
00:13:46,276 --> 00:13:46,901
少校
Major.

216
00:13:48,778 --> 00:13:51,781
我们已经向我们神圣的母亲
传达了你的请求
We have conveyed your
request to our divine mother,

217
00:13:51,823 --> 00:13:54,576
虽然她并没有怀疑你们行动的正义性,
and although she does not doubt
the righteousness of your mission,

218
00:13:54,617 --> 00:13:58,955
我恐怕还是要说, 她不会允许
除了她的子民之外的其他人居住在这里
I'm afraid she cannot countenance
any other people but hers settling here.

219
00:13:58,997 --> 00:14:01,583
你真的需要总是"唱"得这么好听么?
And you really had to chant
all that time to come up with that?

220
00:14:01,624 --> 00:14:02,792
McKay.
McKay.

221
00:14:02,834 --> 00:14:05,169
我们有没有办法请求Athar重新考虑一下?
Is there any way we can
ask Athar to reconsider?

222
00:14:05,211 --> 00:14:10,675
Athar 理解且也很认同
那些幽灵是我们星球当中的灾难
Athar understands and sympathizes
these Wraith are a scourge among our stars

223
00:14:10,717 --> 00:14:14,596
不过她必须把她自己人民的生命放在第一位
but she has to place the
lives of her people first.

224
00:14:15,805 --> 00:14:18,057
好吧, 我想我们在来这里很久之前
Well, I think we both knew
what you were going to say

225
00:14:18,099 --> 00:14:19,475
就已经都知道了你准备说的了
long before you even went in there.

226
00:14:19,559 --> 00:14:21,269
我们祈求Athar的指引
We prayed for Athar's guidance.

227
00:14:21,311 --> 00:14:22,896
那么Athar是怎么说的?
And what did Athar say?

228
00:14:23,980 --> 00:14:27,817
你们藏在你们所谓的信仰背后
来证明你们完完全全的自私自利
You're hiding behind your religion to
justify your complete and utter selfishness.

229
00:14:27,859 --> 00:14:28,735
Rodney...
Rodney...

230
00:14:28,776 --> 00:14:31,696
如果 Athar 确实存在, 她自己也会觉得羞愧
if Athar existed, she
would be ashamed of herself.

231
00:14:31,738 --> 00:14:35,074
我们只是请求不被打扰, 平静的生活下去
We ask only to be left alone and in peace.

232
00:14:35,116 --> 00:14:38,912
所有数不清的成千上万的, 甚至上百万的
人就应该死去
So untold thousands, possibly millions
of people will die out there

233
00:14:38,953 --> 00:14:40,830
在他们可以被一个叫做Athar的人拯救的时候
when they could have been saved,
all in the name of Athar.

234
00:14:40,872 --> 00:14:42,582
你们可真, 真是平静啊
How very, very peaceful of you.

235
00:14:42,624 --> 00:14:44,292
你应该感激 Athar.
You should be grateful to Athar.

236
00:14:44,334 --> 00:14:45,793
这是在浪费时间
This is a waste of time.

237
00:14:45,835 --> 00:14:47,837
Athar 很抱歉她不能帮助你们
Athar regrets that she cannot help you.

238
00:14:47,879 --> 00:14:49,881
而且我相信这就是她的原话
And I'm sure those were her exact words.

239
00:14:49,923 --> 00:14:50,757
够了
That's enough.

240
00:14:53,176 --> 00:14:54,469
回到飞船那里去
Head back to the jumper.

241
00:14:54,510 --> 00:14:55,929
我过会就来
I'll be there in a minute.

242
00:14:55,970 --> 00:14:56,846
为什么?
Why?

243
00:14:56,888 --> 00:14:57,889
因为你毫无帮助
Because you're not helping.

244
00:14:57,931 --> 00:14:58,932
是的, 长官
Yes, sir.

245
00:15:08,733 --> 00:15:10,401
我很抱歉
I apologize.

246
00:15:10,568 --> 00:15:13,655
他只是心直口快, 我们也是
He acts only in accordance
to his beliefs, as do we.

247
00:15:13,696 --> 00:15:16,991
不过 Rodney 说的没错
But Rodney is right about one thing.

248
00:15:17,033 --> 00:15:20,411
这事关生命,  人类的生命
This really is about lives, human lives.

249
00:15:20,453 --> 00:15:24,123
迟早, 幽灵会出现在亚特兰蒂斯
到那时...
Sooner or later, the Wraith are going to
show up at Atlantis, and when they do...

250
00:15:24,165 --> 00:15:24,999
你是个武士
you're a warrior.

251
00:15:25,041 --> 00:15:27,794
嗯, 我并不了解 "武士"
Well, I don't know about "warrior."

252
00:15:27,835 --> 00:15:29,045
这是你的职业, 少校
It is your vocation, Major.

253
00:15:29,712 --> 00:15:30,838
你将会战斗
You will fight.

254
00:15:31,631 --> 00:15:36,094
我会努力的, 不过要知道我们所面对的
以及获胜的可能性...
I'll try, but knowing what
we're up against, and the odds...

255
00:15:37,804 --> 00:15:46,396
瞧,  如果你能够请求Athar考虑一下
我们也是她的子民, 我会非常感激的
Look I'd appreciate it if you would ask
Athar to consider that we are her people.

256
00:15:46,437 --> 00:15:51,025
即便我们来自很远的地方, 我们都是相同的
Even though we come from
very far away, we're the same.

257
00:15:51,067 --> 00:15:54,028
我们都是人类, 这就是说我们不是陌生人
We're human, which means we're not strangers.

258
00:15:54,070 --> 00:15:54,988
我们是一家人
We're family.

259
00:16:04,372 --> 00:16:05,582
傍晚的微风
Evening breeze.

260
00:16:06,916 --> 00:16:09,544
我希望这是 Athar 的某种暗示
I was kind of hoping
it was a sign from Athar.

261
00:16:09,586 --> 00:16:12,171
你的话非常有说服力, Sheppard 少校
Your words are most
compelling, Major Sheppard.

262
00:16:12,213 --> 00:16:13,256
谢谢
Thank you.

263
00:16:13,840 --> 00:16:15,466
我希望能够说服
I was going for compelling.

264
00:16:15,842 --> 00:16:17,969
你真的认为我们是一家人?
Do you truly believe we are family?

265
00:16:18,011 --> 00:16:19,137
我们是
We are.

266
00:16:19,178 --> 00:16:20,471
我可以证明给你看
I can prove it to you.

267
00:16:20,513 --> 00:16:21,347
怎么证明?
How?

268
00:16:21,389 --> 00:16:22,765
回到亚特兰蒂斯
Come back to Atlantis.

269
00:16:22,807 --> 00:16:24,350
看我们真正是谁
See who we really are.

270
00:16:24,392 --> 00:16:26,436
一旦 Athar 了解我们更多...
Once Athar learns more about us...

271
00:16:26,477 --> 00:16:27,520
这可以接受
this is acceptable.

272
00:16:28,021 --> 00:16:29,022
是么?
It is?

273
00:16:29,355 --> 00:16:33,443
Chaya, 求你了, 你不能离开
Chaya, please, you cannot leave.

274
00:16:33,484 --> 00:16:38,031
Athar 永远和我们在一起
无论我们在哪里, Zarah.
Athar is with us always,
no matter where we are, Zarah.

275
00:16:43,912 --> 00:16:45,079
我明白了
I understand.

276
00:16:45,121 --> 00:16:51,711
我准备好了
I am ready.

277
00:16:55,798 --> 00:16:57,383
欢迎来到亚特兰蒂斯
Welcome to Atlantis.

278
00:16:57,634 --> 00:16:58,676
谢谢
Thank you.

279
00:16:58,927 --> 00:17:02,013
希望你不要介意
不过我们的医生确实需要对所有外星成员
I hope you don't mind, but our
doctors do require a medical exam

280
00:17:02,055 --> 00:17:03,765
以及我们的访问者
of all off-planet team members

281
00:17:03,806 --> 00:17:06,976
进行医学检查
不过在那之后, 你就可以四处参观一下了
and our visitors, but after that,
perhaps you'd like a full tour.

282
00:17:07,018 --> 00:17:07,977
我会喜欢的
I would love that.

283
00:17:08,019 --> 00:17:10,313
Sheppard 少校已经同意这样做了
Major Sheppard has
already promised to do so.

284
00:17:10,355 --> 00:17:11,773
当然他会的
Of course he has.

285
00:17:11,814 --> 00:17:12,649
当然我会
Of course I have.

286
00:17:12,690 --> 00:17:15,318
请随我到医务室...
Please, if you'll
follow me to the infirmary...

287
00:17:15,360 --> 00:17:17,946
也许我应该跟着
如果你有什么问题的话
maybe I should tag along,
in case you have any questions..

288
00:17:17,987 --> 00:17:19,155
我想我已经搞定了, Rodney.
I think I've got a handle, Rodney.

289
00:17:19,197 --> 00:17:20,531
有很多系统你完全...
There are a lot of systems you know absolutely...

290
00:17:20,573 --> 00:17:21,324
都了解了
Got it covered.

291
00:17:24,327 --> 00:17:24,869
好吧
Fine.

292
00:17:34,587 --> 00:17:35,421
不要动
Hold still.

293
00:17:35,463 --> 00:17:37,215
只要一会儿
Just a minute more.

294
00:17:39,884 --> 00:17:44,180
好了, 亲爱的, 看起来里面的你跟外面一样可爱
Well, my dear, it seems you're just as
lovely on the inside as you are on the out.

295
00:17:44,222 --> 00:17:47,225
如果健康是美丽的同义词
If health is synonymous with beauty.

296
00:17:47,267 --> 00:17:48,601
你可以起来了
You can get up now.

297
00:17:48,643 --> 00:17:50,436
这个设备是如何
How does this device

298
00:17:50,478 --> 00:17:51,980
按照你说的去做的?
do what you say it does?

299
00:17:52,272 --> 00:17:57,902
它建立你身体内部组织的图像
它们都是非常完美的图像
It creates images of the tissues inside
your body, and they are picture-perfect.

300
00:17:57,944 --> 00:18:00,488
这些机器是从你们的星球上带来的么?
Did you bring these
machines back from your world?

301
00:18:00,530 --> 00:18:01,406
有些是
Some.

302
00:18:01,447 --> 00:18:05,076
其他的则是亚特兰蒂斯人的技术
我们只是知道怎么使用, 还有一些...
Others are atlantean technology that
we've figured out how to use, and a few...

303
00:18:05,118 --> 00:18:09,038
嗯, 我甚至根本不知道它们是做什么的
well, I haven't the vaguest idea what they do.

304
00:18:09,080 --> 00:18:11,040
希望某天我能够和他们当中的某个会会面
Hopefully one day I'll have a chance to meet one.

305
00:18:11,082 --> 00:18:11,916
我亲自去问问他们
I'll ask them myself.

306
00:18:11,958 --> 00:18:13,251
你知道他们发生了什么?
Do you know what happened to them?

307
00:18:13,293 --> 00:18:16,713
嗯, 在和幽灵的战争之后
有一些回到了地球
Well, some returned to Earth
after the war with the Wraith.

308
00:18:16,754 --> 00:18:19,924
这就是我们知道的了
不过我们还知道他们当中有些人升天了
That much we know, but we also
know that some of them ascended.

309
00:18:20,341 --> 00:18:21,426
升天?
Ascended?

310
00:18:21,467 --> 00:18:24,429
进入一个更高的层次
在那里他们仅仅以能量的形式存在
To a higher plane,
where they exist only as energy.

311
00:18:25,722 --> 00:18:27,849
你那个星球中的所有人都跟你一样健康么?
Are all the people of
your world as healthy as you?

312
00:18:28,892 --> 00:18:29,642
是的
Yes.

313
00:18:30,977 --> 00:18:32,103
没有疾病?
No disease, ailments?

314
00:18:33,479 --> 00:18:35,273
从来没有人摔断腿?
No one ever breaks a leg?

315
00:18:35,315 --> 00:18:37,984
这种事情很少
不过我的人民很快就会痊愈了
Such things are rare,
but my people heal quite rapidly.

316
00:18:38,192 --> 00:18:39,694
真的?
Really?

317
00:18:42,822 --> 00:18:43,781
我们完了么?
Are we done?

318
00:18:44,574 --> 00:18:45,199
完了么?
Are we?

319
00:18:45,325 --> 00:18:47,118
我见过的最健康的病人了
Healthiest patient I've ever had.

320
00:18:47,160 --> 00:18:48,161
你可以走了, 亲爱的
Off you go, love.

321
00:18:53,917 --> 00:18:54,709
情况到底怎样?
Where are we at?

322
00:18:54,751 --> 00:18:56,753
好吧, 要么她知道武器在哪里
却故意在玩弄我们
Well, either she knows where
the weapon is and she's playing us,

323
00:18:56,836 --> 00:18:59,881
要么她确实不知道
不管是哪种情况, 我们都在浪费时间
or else she has no idea,
in which case, we are wasting our time.

324
00:18:59,923 --> 00:19:01,007
那么你的建议是?
So what do you suggest?

325
00:19:01,049 --> 00:19:04,427
派另外一对人乘飞船过去
扫描那个行星上的能量信号
Take another team back in the jumper,
scan the planet for energy signatures.

326
00:19:04,469 --> 00:19:06,221
Chaya的人民不会察觉我们在轨道上所做的事情
Chaya's people won't have a
clue what we're doing from orbit,

327
00:19:06,262 --> 00:19:08,640
除非他们已经有了发达的科技
只是假装出来不是这样
unless they're a technically advanced
race that are pretending not to be,

328
00:19:08,681 --> 00:19:10,850
